The paper discusses the interactions between privacy and accuracy in machine learning, using the frameworks of empirical risk minimization, differential privacy, and Stackelberg games. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography and security (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
